.TH "svc_rdma_pages_write" 9 "svc_rdma_pages_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
svc_rdma_pages_write \- Construct RDMA Writes from pages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" svc_rdma_pages_write
.BI "(struct svc_rdma_write_info *info "  ","
.BI "const struct xdr_buf *xdr "  ","
.BI "unsigned int offset "  ","
.BI "unsigned long length "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "info" 12
pointer to write arguments
.IP "xdr" 12
xdr_buf with pages to write
.IP "offset" 12
offset into the content of \fIxdr\fP
.IP "length" 12
number of bytes to write
.SH "RETURN"
On succes, returns zero
-E2BIG if the client-provided Write chunk is too small
-ENOMEM if a resource has been exhausted
-EIO if an rdma-rw error occurred
